B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                      FY 2024    FY 2025     FY 2026
- Provide limited Missile Defense System-level engineering support, to include alignment of system and subsystem technical
requirements, limited Glide Phase Interceptor lethality support, and development of HD/Glide Phase Interceptor-specific M&S
updates.
- Mature technology to address current and future hypersonic threats.
FY 2026 Plans:
Aegis Weapon System
- Evolve and mature systems engineering efforts to continue the flow of system level requirements to subsystem requirement
specifications and continue preliminary design activities.
- Develop updated weapon system code to support demonstration of capability in partner flight tests and flight experiments and
leverage results of flight tests enhance Glide Phase Interceptor designs and inform future development.
- Continue refinement of engagement and shot selection algorithms to optimize performance across the Glide Phase Interceptor
threat and battlespace.

Missile System
- Continue to evolve and mature a single missile system design.
- Build and test early subsystem design prototype hardware to mature designs toward the preliminary design.
- Continue to execute the cooperative development agreement with the Japan Ministry of Defense partner.
- Integration into Golden Dome communication architecture.

Engineering Enablers
- Provide limited Missile Defense System-level engineering support, to include alignment of system and subsystem technical
requirements, limited Glide Phase Interceptor lethality support, and development of HD/Glide Phase Interceptor-specific M&S
updates.
- Mature technology to address current and future hypersonic threats.
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase from FY 2025 to FY 2026 accelerates delivery of GPI capability from mid-2030s to 2032 which supports Golden Dome
for America/Regional Defense and provides for the transition of the program requirements allocation and system design to
development and testing of preliminary design hardware and software builds. Hypersonic technology maturation, risk reduction
and system engineering activities will be completed to support preliminary design development and testing of the missile concept.
Aegis Weapon System upgrades to leverage the Glide Phase Interceptor for regional hypersonic glide phase defense will continue
to mature including work toward system level preliminary design incorporating one missile concept and the development of
weapon system code for demonstration in early flight experiments.
